records.addlTxt: Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for LEVEL 5 SUPERVISION. Defendant must make all court appearances.  NO CONTACT with Cousin Subs on 4121 N 56th St and victim ADR. No use or possession of firearms/weapons.

Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and Defense acknowledged receipt of Criminal Complaint.  Defendant pled not guilty.  

Arguments heard as to bail.  Court set cash bail with TURNOVER to Justice Point for LEVEL 5 SUPERVISION.  Court scheduled a preliminary hearing.  Case adjourned to Branch PE, Rm 146 CJF.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Traevon Elijuawon Young appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Jason A Findling in court for Traevon Elijuawon Young.  Attorney Amanda Kirklewski in court on behalf of Attorney Gerald Henry Alder for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a Doctor's Report Return.  Parties do not contest the Doctor's findings.  Court held colloquy with Mr. Young.  Court adopts the findings and proceeded with Initial Appearance.
Received and Filed: Competency Report Dated 10/25/22
Signed and filed: Order for INPATIENT Competency Examination
Received and Filed: Proposed Order for INPATIENT Competency Examination

Defendant Traevon Elijuawon Young appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Jason A Findling in court for Traevon Elijuawon Young.  Attorney James C Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a Doctor's Report Return.  Doctor Jenna Goebel is unable to render an opinion regarding Mr. Young's competency at this time and recommends transfer to an appropriate state psychiatric facility for an inpatient evaluation.  No objection from the parties.  Court adopts the Doctor's findings and orders an INPATIENT examination.  Order for Competency signed and filed by the Court.  Case adjourned for a Doctor's Report Return in Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed: Doctor's Report Dated 09-21-2022

Attorney Jason A Findling in court, defendant Traevon Elijuawon Young not in court, in custody.  Gerald Henry Alder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: STW
CASE HELD VIA ZOOM. Case set for Doctor's Report Return. Parties in receipt of Dr. Goebel's report and do not contest findings for an additional evaluation. Defense will remind his client to cooperate with the doctor. Case adjourned, Branch 38.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for September 23, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Forensic evaluation ordered.  INITIAL APPEARANCE NOT HELD.  Trial court to address INITIAL APPEARANCE.

Defendant Traevon Elijuawon Young in court with attorney Jason A Findling.  Defendant Traevon Elijuawon Young in custody.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Traevon Elijuawon Young appeared by video means with Attorney.  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 2.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Commissioner tolls the time limits for the preliminary hearing.
This hearing may be streamed live at the discretion of the Court on https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/c5e6133e-7164-4e97-66e6-4c87ef70fbdb  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for August 10, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Order for Competency Examination, signed and filed.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
